        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 3:28PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 328 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Commerce City, or 10 miles northeast of Denver, moving east at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Denver, Aurora, Thornton, eastern Arvada, southeastern
Westminster, Broomfield, Commerce City, Northglenn, Brighton,
northern Englewood, Federal Heights, Denver International Airport,
D.I.A Terminal and Concourses, Buckley SFB, Barr Lake, Todd Creek,
Watkins and Henderson.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
